rs to private renting, the impact on public expenditure and on the current housing situation, addresses the proposals for new legislation and details the potential impact of these. It is an essential read for anyone interested in this highly topical issue.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPublic housingxGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831111964350 cprintz978144733207740uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447332084?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447332084423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447332084/original  a978-3-11-119643-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles